Single-database configuration for Flask.

Features to Implement
Admin Dashboard:

View all users and their activities.

Delete users or messages.

Monitor group chats.

User Features:

Real-Time Chat: One-on-one and group chats.

Status Updates: Users can set a status (e.g., "Hey there! I am using TomChat").

Last Seen: Show when a user was last active.

Profile Management: Users can update their profile (username, password, status).

Message Read Receipts: Show when a message is read.

Typing Indicators: Show when a user is typing.

File Sharing: Allow users to send images, videos, and documents.

Group Chats: Create and manage group chats.

Security:

Admin can ban users or delete inappropriate messages.

End-to-end encryption for messages (optional, advanced feature).
